## Output Filename Logic

| Template name pattern | Generated output name |
|---|---|
| `ResumeT - {Company name} - {Position name} - Wang Cuixia - {Generate date}.docx` | `Resume - AUT auto - Sales Consultant - WangCuixia - 20260226.docx` |
| `Cover LetterT - {Company name} - {Position name} - {Name of applicant} - {Generate date}.docx` | `Cover Letter - AUT auto - Sales Consultant - WangCuixia - 20260226.docx` |
| `ResumeT - {公司名称} - {职位名称} - 王翠霞 - {Generate date}.docx` | `Resume - AUT auto - 销售顾问 - 王翠霞 - 20260226.docx` |

Rules:
- [ResumeT](file:///c:/scripts/build/search_agent/backend/app/models/template.py#4-15) → [Resume](file:///c:/scripts/build/search_agent/backend/app/models/template.py#4-15)
- `Cover LetterT` → `Cover Letter`
- `{Company name}` / `{公司名称}` → actual `job.company`
- `{Position name}` / `{职位名称}` → actual `job.title`
- `{Name of applicant}` → user's name (from `job.user_email` profile, or hardcoded from template filename non-placeholder parts)
- `{Generate date}` → today's date in `YYYYMMDD` format

---

## Placeholder Syntax Supported

| Syntax in .docx | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `{skills}` | Simple replacement, LLM decides format |
| `{projects: "list 3 key projects"}` | `projects` is the key, the quoted text is the generation instruction |
| `{Content of Cover letter: 4 paragraphs, 1 page}` | Full sentence key with instructions |
| `{skills: "skills"}` | Redundant but supported |

Regex to extract: `\{([^}]+)\}` — capture everything inside braces, then split on `:` to separate key from instructions.

---

## What Does NOT Change

- The LLM content quality and experience-block matching logic
- The job analysis, company research flows  
- The experience library (ExperienceLibrary.tsx)
- Authentication and all other API endpoints
- The database schema (no migration needed)
- Chinese / English language switching logic
- The existing markdown fallback (if user has old .md templates, they still work)

